value: Resident, tall reed beds and swamps: L. Chad (chadensis); small isolated populations in N Nigeria, S Nigeria and S Cameroon, and then NE DRC - SW Uganda, Burundi (centralis), S Sudan (sudanensis); parts of Ethiopia (abyssinicus); parts of W Angola (benguellensis); SW and SE Kenya - S Tanzania mainly near coast; E and S DRC, SE Angola, N Botswana east to L. Malawi and south down E and S coasts of South Africa (other races).
males and females share resources on their territory only during the breeding season
